aima.core.logic.propositional.parsing.ast

Class PropositionSymbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • aima.core.logic.propositional.parsing.ast.Sentence
      • aima.core.logic.propositional.parsing.ast.AtomicSentence
        • aima.core.logic.propositional.parsing.ast.PropositionSymbol
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParseTreeNode

    public class PropositionSymbol
extends AtomicSentence
    Artificial Intelligence A Modern Approach (3rd Edition): page 244.

    Proposition Symbol: Each such symbol stands for a proposition that can be true or false. There are two proposition symbols with fixed meanings: True the always-true proposition and False the always-false proposition.

    Note: While the book states:
    'We use symbols that start with an upper case letter and may contain other letters or subscripts'. In this implementation we allow any legal java identifier to stand in for a proposition symbol.
    Author:
    Ciaran O'Reilly, Ravi Mohan
    See Also:
    SourceVersion.isIdentifier(CharSequence)
